	body
		div.container-fluid
			div.row
				div.col-md-12
					h2 API Basejump: Timestamp microservice
					
					blockquote User stories:
						p.story-item 1) I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016)
						p.story-item 2) If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
						p.story-item 3) If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
						
					h3 Example usage:
					p
						code https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/December%2015,%202015
					p
						code https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/1450137600

					h3 Example output:
					p
						code { "unix": 1450137600, "natural": "December 15, 2015" }
					
					br
					hr
					p Source code found at <a href="">github</a>.
		
